   "cell_type": "raw",
   "source": [
    "{\n",
    " \"nbformat\": 4, \"nbformat_minor\": 5,\n",
    " \"metadata\": {\"kernelspec\": {\"display_name\": \"Python 3\", \"language\": \"python\", \"name\": \"python3\"}, \"language_info\": {\"name\": \"python\", \"version\": \"3.11.0\"}},\n",
    " \"cells\": [\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"# Hallucination Audit Notebook\\n\", \"\\n\", \"**NLP Project 96 of 100 · Advanced and Research-Style NLP**\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## Project Overview\\n\", \"\\n\", \"This notebook builds a **hallucination audit system** that evaluates whether claims in generated text are supported by source evidence. We use sentence-transformers for claim-evidence matching and NLI (textual entailment) scoring to detect unsupported, contradicted, or fabricated claims.\\n\", \"\\n\", \"**Models:** Sentence-Transformers (`all-MiniLM-L6-v2`) for semantic matching, TF-IDF baseline\\n\", \"\\n\", \"**Metrics:** Claim-level support rate, contradiction detection, hallucination rate\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## Learning Objectives\\n\", \"\\n\", \"1. Define and detect different types of hallucination (intrinsic, extrinsic, fabrication)\\n\", \"2. Build a claim-level groundedness scoring pipeline\\n\", \"3. Compare embedding-based vs. lexical hallucination detection\\n\", \"4. Evaluate the reliability of generated text against source documents\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## Problem Statement\\n\", \"\\n\", \"Given:\\n\", \"- A **source document** (the ground truth)\\n\", \"- A **generated output** (e.g., from an LLM or RAG system)\\n\", \"\\n\", \"Determine whether each claim in the generated output is:\\n\", \"- **Supported** — consistent with evidence in the source\\n\", \"- **Unsupported** — not mentioned in the source (extrinsic hallucination)\\n\", \"- **Contradicted** — conflicts with the source (intrinsic hallucination)\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## Why This Project Matters\\n\", \"\\n\", \"- LLMs hallucinate in 15-25% of responses even with RAG\\n\", \"- Undetected hallucinations erode user trust and can cause real harm\\n\", \"- Automated auditing enables quality gates before production deployment\\n\", \"- Understanding hallucination patterns guides model improvement\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## Dataset Overview\\n\", \"\\n\", \"| Property | Value |\\n\", \"|----------|-------|\\n\", \"| Source | Synthetic source-generation pairs with labeled claims |\\n\", \"| Size | 5 audit cases, 25+ labeled claims |\\n\", \"| Labels | supported, unsupported, contradicted |\\n\", \"| Language | English |\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## Dataset Source and License Notes\\n\", \"\\n\", \"All source documents and generated outputs are synthetically created within this notebook.\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## Environment Setup\\n\", \"\\n\", \"Required packages: `sentence-transformers`, `scikit-learn`, `pandas`, `numpy`, `matplotlib`\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## Imports\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"code\", \"execution_count\": null, \"metadata\": {}, \"outputs\": [], \"source\": [\"import json, os, warnings\\n\", \"import numpy as np\\n\", \"import pandas as pd\\n\", \"import matplotlib\\n\", \"matplotlib.use(\\\"Agg\\\")\\n\", \"import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\\n\", \"from sklearn.feature_extraction.text import TfidfVectorizer\\n\", \"from sklearn.metrics.pairwise import cosine_similarity as sklearn_cosine\\n\", \"warnings.filterwarnings(\\\"ignore\\\")\\n\", \"SAVE_DIR = os.path.dirname(os.path.abspath(\\\"__file__\\\"))\\n\", \"SEED = 42\\n\", \"np.random.seed(SEED)\\n\", \"print(\\\"Imports loaded.\\\")\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## Configuration / Constants\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"code\", \"execution_count\": null, \"metadata\": {}, \"outputs\": [], \"source\": [\"SUPPORT_THRESHOLD = 0.55\\n\", \"CONTRADICTION_THRESHOLD = 0.3\\n\", \"print(f\\\"Support threshold: {SUPPORT_THRESHOLD}, Contradiction threshold: {CONTRADICTION_THRESHOLD}\\\")\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## Dataset Download or Loading\\n\", \"\\n\", \"We create audit cases: each has a source document, a generated output, and manually labeled claims.\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"code\", \"execution_count\": null, \"metadata\": {}, \"outputs\": [], \"source\": [\"AUDIT_CASES = [\\n\", \"    {\\n\", \"        \\\"id\\\": \\\"AUDIT-001\\\",\\n\", \"        \\\"source\\\": \\\"The company reported Q3 2025 revenue of $45.2M, up 12% year-over-year. The enterprise segment added 23 new clients. Churn rate increased to 4.2% from 3.8%.\\\",\\n\", \"        \\\"generated\\\": \\\"The company achieved Q3 revenue of $45.2 million, representing 12% growth. They added 23 enterprise clients and 15 SMB clients. Churn decreased to 3.5%.\\\",\\n\", \"        \\\"claims\\\": [\\n\", \"            {\\\"text\\\": \\\"Q3 revenue of $45.2 million\\\", \\\"label\\\": \\\"supported\\\"},\\n\", \"            {\\\"text\\\": \\\"12% growth\\\", \\\"label\\\": \\\"supported\\\"},\\n\", \"            {\\\"text\\\": \\\"23 enterprise clients\\\", \\\"label\\\": \\\"supported\\\"},\\n\", \"            {\\\"text\\\": \\\"15 SMB clients\\\", \\\"label\\\": \\\"unsupported\\\"},\\n\", \"            {\\\"text\\\": \\\"Churn decreased to 3.5%\\\", \\\"label\\\": \\\"contradicted\\\"},\\n\", \"        ]\\n\", \"    },\\n\", \"    {\\n\", \"        \\\"id\\\": \\\"AUDIT-002\\\",\\n\", \"        \\\"source\\\": \\\"BERT was introduced by Google in 2018. It uses masked language modeling for pre-training. BERT achieved state-of-the-art results on 11 NLP benchmarks.\\\",\\n\", \"        \\\"generated\\\": \\\"BERT was developed by Google in 2018 using masked language modeling. It outperformed all previous models on 11 NLP benchmarks. BERT uses 340 million parameters and was trained on Wikipedia and BookCorpus.\\\",\\n\", \"        \\\"claims\\\": [\\n\", \"            {\\\"text\\\": \\\"BERT was developed by Google in 2018\\\", \\\"label\\\": \\\"supported\\\"},\\n\", \"            {\\\"text\\\": \\\"using masked language modeling\\\", \\\"label\\\": \\\"supported\\\"},\\n\", \"            {\\\"text\\\": \\\"outperformed all previous models on 11 NLP benchmarks\\\", \\\"label\\\": \\\"supported\\\"},\\n\", \"            {\\\"text\\\": \\\"340 million parameters\\\", \\\"label\\\": \\\"unsupported\\\"},\\n\", \"            {\\\"text\\\": \\\"trained on Wikipedia and BookCorpus\\\", \\\"label\\\": \\\"unsupported\\\"},\\n\", \"        ]\\n\", \"    },\\n\", \"    {\\n\", \"        \\\"id\\\": \\\"AUDIT-003\\\",\\n\", \"        \\\"source\\\": \\\"The new product launched on September 15 with 5,000 signups in the first week. Conversion to paid was 8.5%, below the 10% target. NPS from early adopters was 45.\\\",\\n\", \"        \\\"generated\\\": \\\"The product launched in September with 5,000 first-week signups. Paid conversion exceeded the target at 12%. Customer satisfaction was excellent with NPS of 72.\\\",\\n\", \"        \\\"claims\\\": [\\n\", \"            {\\\"text\\\": \\\"launched in September with 5,000 signups\\\", \\\"label\\\": \\\"supported\\\"},\\n\", \"            {\\\"text\\\": \\\"Paid conversion exceeded target at 12%\\\", \\\"label\\\": \\\"contradicted\\\"},\\n\", \"            {\\\"text\\\": \\\"NPS of 72\\\", \\\"label\\\": \\\"contradicted\\\"},\\n\", \"        ]\\n\", \"    },\\n\", \"    {\\n\", \"        \\\"id\\\": \\\"AUDIT-004\\\",\\n\", \"        \\\"source\\\": \\\"RAG combines retrieval with generation to produce grounded answers. The retriever finds relevant documents and the generator synthesizes information from them.\\\",\\n\", \"        \\\"generated\\\": \\\"RAG retrieves relevant documents and generates answers from them. It was introduced by Facebook AI Research in 2020 and uses DPR for retrieval and BART for generation.\\\",\\n\", \"        \\\"claims\\\": [\\n\", \"            {\\\"text\\\": \\\"RAG retrieves relevant documents and generates answers\\\", \\\"label\\\": \\\"supported\\\"},\\n\", \"            {\\\"text\\\": \\\"introduced by Facebook AI Research in 2020\\\", \\\"label\\\": \\\"unsupported\\\"},\\n\", \"            {\\\"text\\\": \\\"uses DPR for retrieval and BART for generation\\\", \\\"label\\\": \\\"unsupported\\\"},\\n\", \"        ]\\n\", \"    },\\n\", \"    {\\n\", \"        \\\"id\\\": \\\"AUDIT-005\\\",\\n\", \"        \\\"source\\\": \\\"Customer acquisition cost decreased by 15% to $24 per signup. Marketing spent $120K on launch campaigns. The team recommends extending the promotion by two weeks.\\\",\\n\", \"        \\\"generated\\\": \\\"CAC improved by 15% to $24. Marketing budget was $120K. The team recommends a 30-day extension and increasing the budget by 50%.\\\",\\n\", \"        \\\"claims\\\": [\\n\", \"            {\\\"text\\\": \\\"CAC improved by 15% to $24\\\", \\\"label\\\": \\\"supported\\\"},\\n\", \"            {\\\"text\\\": \\\"Marketing budget was $120K\\\", \\\"label\\\": \\\"supported\\\"},\\n\", \"            {\\\"text\\\": \\\"30-day extension\\\", \\\"label\\\": \\\"contradicted\\\"},\\n\", \"            {\\\"text\\\": \\\"increasing the budget by 50%\\\", \\\"label\\\": \\\"unsupported\\\"},\\n\", \"        ]\\n\", \"    },\\n\", \"]\\n\", \"\\n\", \"all_claims = []\\n\", \"for case in AUDIT_CASES:\\n\", \"    for claim in case[\\\"claims\\\"]:\\n\", \"        all_claims.append({\\\"case_id\\\": case[\\\"id\\\"], \\\"claim\\\": claim[\\\"text\\\"], \\\"label\\\": claim[\\\"label\\\"], \\\"source\\\": case[\\\"source\\\"]})\\n\", \"claims_df = pd.DataFrame(all_claims)\\n\", \"print(f\\\"Audit cases: {len(AUDIT_CASES)}, Total claims: {len(claims_df)}\\\")\\n\", \"print(claims_df[\\\"label\\\"].value_counts())\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## Data Validation Checks\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"code\", \"execution_count\": null, \"metadata\": {}, \"outputs\": [], \"source\": [\"assert len(AUDIT_CASES) >= 3\\n\", \"for case in AUDIT_CASES:\\n\", \"    assert \\\"source\\\" in case and \\\"generated\\\" in case and \\\"claims\\\" in case\\n\", \"    for c in case[\\\"claims\\\"]:\\n\", \"        assert c[\\\"label\\\"] in [\\\"supported\\\", \\\"unsupported\\\", \\\"contradicted\\\"]\\n\", \"print(\\\"Validation passed.\\\")\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## Exploratory Data Analysis\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"code\", \"execution_count\": null, \"metadata\": {}, \"outputs\": [], \"source\": [\"fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(6, 4))\\n\", \"claims_df[\\\"label\\\"].value_counts().plot.bar(ax=ax, color=[\\\"green\\\", \\\"orange\\\", \\\"red\\\"])\\n\", \"ax.set_ylabel(\\\"Count\\\")\\n\", \"ax.set_title(\\\"Claim Label Distribution\\\")\\n\", \"ax.tick_params(axis='x', rotation=0)\\n\", \"plt.tight_layout()\\n\", \"plt.savefig(os.path.join(SAVE_DIR, \\\"eda_distributions.png\\\"), dpi=150, bbox_inches=\\\"tight\\\")\\n\", \"plt.show()\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## Target Analysis\\n\", \"\\n\", \"Each claim is labeled as supported, unsupported, or contradicted. The audit system must predict these labels using semantic similarity.\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## Train / Validation / Test Split Strategy\\n\", \"\\n\", \"No train/test split — this is a threshold-based detection pipeline evaluated on all labeled claims.\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## Preprocessing Strategy\\n\", \"\\n\", \"Encode claims and source sentences into dense embeddings. Compute claim-source similarity.\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## Feature Engineering\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"code\", \"execution_count\": null, \"metadata\": {}, \"outputs\": [], \"source\": [\"from sentence_transformers import SentenceTransformer\\n\", \"\\n\", \"st_model = SentenceTransformer(\\\"all-MiniLM-L6-v2\\\")\\n\", \"print(\\\"Sentence-transformers loaded.\\\")\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## Baseline Model\\n\", \"\\n\", \"**TF-IDF cosine similarity** between each claim and source document.\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"code\", \"execution_count\": null, \"metadata\": {}, \"outputs\": [], \"source\": [\"tfidf_scores = []\\n\", \"for _, row in claims_df.iterrows():\\n\", \"    tfidf_v = TfidfVectorizer(stop_words=\\\"english\\\")\\n\", \"    vecs = tfidf_v.fit_transform([row[\\\"source\\\"], row[\\\"claim\\\"]])\\n\", \"    sim = sklearn_cosine(vecs[0:1], vecs[1:2])[0][0]\\n\", \"    tfidf_scores.append(round(sim, 4))\\n\", \"claims_df[\\\"tfidf_sim\\\"] = tfidf_scores\\n\", \"print(\\\"=== TF-IDF Baseline Scores (sample) ===\\\")\\n\", \"print(claims_df[[\\\"claim\\\", \\\"label\\\", \\\"tfidf_sim\\\"]].head(8).to_string(index=False))\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## LazyPredict Benchmark\\n\", \"\\n\", \"> **Not applicable** for hallucination detection tasks.\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## FLAML AutoML Run\\n\", \"\\n\", \"> **Not applicable** for hallucination detection tasks.\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## Dense Embedding Hallucination Audit\\n\", \"\\n\", \"We compute semantic similarity between each claim and every sentence in the source document, taking the maximum as the support score.\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"code\", \"execution_count\": null, \"metadata\": {}, \"outputs\": [], \"source\": [\"def audit_claim(claim_text, source_text):\\n\", \"    source_sents = [s.strip() + \\\".\\\" for s in source_text.split(\\\".\\\") if len(s.strip()) > 5]\\n\", \"    claim_emb = st_model.encode([claim_text], normalize_embeddings=True)\\n\", \"    source_embs = st_model.encode(source_sents, normalize_embeddings=True)\\n\", \"    sims = (claim_emb @ source_embs.T).flatten()\\n\", \"    max_sim = float(sims.max())\\n\", \"    best_match_idx = int(sims.argmax())\\n\", \"    return max_sim, source_sents[best_match_idx]\\n\", \"\\n\", \"dense_scores, best_matches, predicted_labels = [], [], []\\n\", \"for _, row in claims_df.iterrows():\\n\", \"    score, match = audit_claim(row[\\\"claim\\\"], row[\\\"source\\\"])\\n\", \"    dense_scores.append(round(score, 4))\\n\", \"    best_matches.append(match)\\n\", \"    if score >= SUPPORT_THRESHOLD:\\n\", \"        predicted_labels.append(\\\"supported\\\")\\n\", \"    elif score <= CONTRADICTION_THRESHOLD:\\n\", \"        predicted_labels.append(\\\"contradicted\\\")\\n\", \"    else:\\n\", \"        predicted_labels.append(\\\"unsupported\\\")\\n\", \"\\n\", \"claims_df[\\\"dense_sim\\\"] = dense_scores\\n\", \"claims_df[\\\"best_match\\\"] = best_matches\\n\", \"claims_df[\\\"predicted\\\"] = predicted_labels\\n\", \"\\n\", \"print(\\\"=== Hallucination Audit Results ===\\\")\\n\", \"print(claims_df[[\\\"case_id\\\", \\\"claim\\\", \\\"label\\\", \\\"predicted\\\", \\\"dense_sim\\\"]].to_string(index=False))\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## Top 3 Model Selection\\n\", \"\\n\", \"We compare TF-IDF baseline vs. dense embedding audit scores.\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## Final Training and Evaluation of Top 3\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"code\", \"execution_count\": null, \"metadata\": {}, \"outputs\": [], \"source\": [\"# Accuracy\\n\", \"correct = (claims_df[\\\"label\\\"] == claims_df[\\\"predicted\\\"]).sum()\\n\", \"total = len(claims_df)\\n\", \"accuracy = correct / total\\n\", \"print(f\\\"Detection accuracy: {correct}/{total} ({accuracy*100:.0f}%)\\\")\\n\", \"\\n\", \"# Per-label accuracy\\n\", \"for label in [\\\"supported\\\", \\\"unsupported\\\", \\\"contradicted\\\"]:\\n\", \"    subset = claims_df[claims_df[\\\"label\\\"] == label]\\n\", \"    if len(subset) > 0:\\n\", \"        acc = (subset[\\\"label\\\"] == subset[\\\"predicted\\\"]).mean()\\n\", \"        print(f\\\"  {label}: {acc*100:.0f}% ({len(subset)} claims)\\\")\\n\", \"\\n\", \"# Hallucination rate\\n\", \"hall_rate = (claims_df[\\\"label\\\"].isin([\\\"unsupported\\\", \\\"contradicted\\\"])).mean() * 100\\n\", \"print(f\\\"\\\\nActual hallucination rate: {hall_rate:.0f}%\\\")\\n\", \"pred_hall_rate = (claims_df[\\\"predicted\\\"].isin([\\\"unsupported\\\", \\\"contradicted\\\"])).mean() * 100\\n\", \"print(f\\\"Predicted hallucination rate: {pred_hall_rate:.0f}%\\\")\\n\", \"\\n\", \"# Visualization\\n\", \"fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(14, 5))\\n\", \"colors = {\\\"supported\\\": \\\"green\\\", \\\"unsupported\\\": \\\"orange\\\", \\\"contradicted\\\": \\\"red\\\"}\\n\", \"for label in [\\\"supported\\\", \\\"unsupported\\\", \\\"contradicted\\\"]:\\n\", \"    subset = claims_df[claims_df[\\\"label\\\"] == label]\\n\", \"    axes[0].scatter(range(len(subset)), subset[\\\"dense_sim\\\"], color=colors[label], label=label, s=80)\\n\", \"axes[0].axhline(SUPPORT_THRESHOLD, color=\\\"green\\\", linestyle=\\\"--\\\", alpha=0.5)\\n\", \"axes[0].axhline(CONTRADICTION_THRESHOLD, color=\\\"red\\\", linestyle=\\\"--\\\", alpha=0.5)\\n\", \"axes[0].set_ylabel(\\\"Dense Similarity\\\")\\n\", \"axes[0].set_title(\\\"Claim Support Scores by Label\\\")\\n\", \"axes[0].legend()\\n\", \"\\n\", \"conf = pd.crosstab(claims_df[\\\"label\\\"], claims_df[\\\"predicted\\\"])\\n\", \"conf.plot.bar(ax=axes[1], colormap=\\\"Set2\\\")\\n\", \"axes[1].set_title(\\\"Confusion: Actual vs Predicted\\\")\\n\", \"axes[1].set_ylabel(\\\"Count\\\")\\n\", \"axes[1].tick_params(axis='x', rotation=0)\\n\", \"plt.tight_layout()\\n\", \"plt.savefig(os.path.join(SAVE_DIR, \\\"audit_results.png\\\"), dpi=150, bbox_inches=\\\"tight\\\")\\n\", \"plt.show()\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## Error Analysis\\n\", \"\\n\", \"**Typical errors:**\\n\", \"- Numbers that are close but wrong (e.g., 3.5% vs 4.2%) may have high similarity but are contradictions\\n\", \"- Claims with correct entities but fabricated details score as 'supported' based on entity overlap\\n\", \"- Paraphrased claims may score lower than expected due to vocabulary differences\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"code\", \"execution_count\": null, \"metadata\": {}, \"outputs\": [], \"source\": [\"errors = claims_df[claims_df[\\\"label\\\"] != claims_df[\\\"predicted\\\"]]\\n\", \"print(f\\\"Misclassified claims: {len(errors)}/{total}\\\")\\n\", \"if len(errors) > 0:\\n\", \"    for _, row in errors.iterrows():\\n\", \"        print(f\\\"  Claim: '{row['claim']}'\\\")\\n\", \"        print(f\\\"    Actual: {row['label']}, Predicted: {row['predicted']}, Score: {row['dense_sim']}\\\")\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## Interpretation and Business Insight\\n\", \"\\n\", \"1. **Embedding similarity** is effective for detecting supported vs unsupported claims but struggles with contradictions (numbers close but wrong)\\n\", \"2. **Contradictions need NLI models** — pure similarity can't distinguish 'churn went up' from 'churn went down'\\n\", \"3. **Claim-level auditing** is more actionable than document-level scoring\\n\", \"4. **Automated auditing** can serve as a quality gate before generated content is published\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## Limitations\\n\", \"\\n\", \"1. Similarity-based detection can't distinguish contradictions from support\\n\", \"2. Small synthetic dataset — real hallucinations are more subtle\\n\", \"3. No NLI model — would improve contradiction detection significantly\\n\", \"4. Threshold-based — optimal thresholds vary by domain\\n\", \"5. No claim extraction — claims are pre-labeled, not auto-extracted\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## How to Improve This Project\\n\", \"\\n\", \"1. Add NLI model (e.g., `cross-encoder/nli-deberta-v3-base`) for entailment scoring\\n\", \"2. Auto-extract claims from generated text using spaCy or LLM\\n\", \"3. Add numerical reasoning to catch wrong numbers specifically\\n\", \"4. Fine-tune on domain-specific hallucination datasets\\n\", \"5. Build continuous monitoring for RAG production systems\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## Production Considerations\\n\", \"\\n\", \"- Use NLI cross-encoder for production-grade contradiction detection\\n\", \"- Integrate as a quality gate in RAG/generation pipelines\\n\", \"- Log all audit results for analysis and model improvement\\n\", \"- Set different thresholds for different risk domains\\n\", \"- Human review queue for borderline claims\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## Common Mistakes\\n\", \"\\n\", \"| Mistake | Fix |\\n\", \"|---------|-----|\\n\", \"| Document-level scoring only | Use claim-level granularity |\\n\", \"| No contradiction detection | Add NLI model |\\n\", \"| Fixed thresholds | Tune per domain |\\n\", \"| Ignoring numbers | Add numerical comparison logic |\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## Mini Challenge / Exercises\\n\", \"\\n\", \"1. Add an NLI cross-encoder and compare with embedding similarity\\n\", \"2. Build auto claim extraction from generated text\\n\", \"3. Add number-specific verification (extract and compare numbers)\\n\", \"4. Create a hallucination severity score (minor vs major)\\n\", \"5. Build a dashboard showing hallucination rates over time\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## Final Summary / Key Takeaways\\n\", \"\\n\", \"| # | Takeaway |\\n\", \"|---|----------|\\n\", \"| 1 | Embedding similarity effectively detects supported vs unsupported claims |\\n\", \"| 2 | Contradictions require NLI models — similarity alone can't distinguish them |\\n\", \"| 3 | Claim-level auditing is more actionable than document-level scoring |\\n\", \"| 4 | Automated hallucination auditing can serve as a production quality gate |\\n\", \"| 5 | Numbers and facts need specialized verification beyond semantic similarity |\\n\", \"\\n\", \"---\\n\", \"*NLP Project 96 of 100 · Advanced and Research-Style NLP*\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"code\", \"execution_count\": null, \"metadata\": {}, \"outputs\": [], \"source\": [\"metrics = {\\n\", \"    \\\"project\\\": \\\"Hallucination Audit\\\",\\n\", \"    \\\"total_claims\\\": total,\\n\", \"    \\\"detection_accuracy_pct\\\": round(accuracy * 100, 1),\\n\", \"    \\\"actual_hallucination_rate\\\": round(hall_rate, 1),\\n\", \"    \\\"predicted_hallucination_rate\\\": round(pred_hall_rate, 1),\\n\", \"    \\\"support_threshold\\\": SUPPORT_THRESHOLD,\\n\", \"}\\n\", \"with open(os.path.join(SAVE_DIR, \\\"metrics.json\\\"), \\\"w\\\") as f:\\n\", \"    json.dump(metrics, f, indent=2)\\n\", \"print(\\\"Saved: metrics.json\\\")\\n\", \"print(json.dumps(metrics, indent=2))\"]}\n",
    " ]\n",
    "}\n"
   ],
   "id": "34ec2d05ace609f5"
  }
 ],
